NODE_4_length_144197_cov_90.594449	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	23314	24129	.	+	0	ID=MGA_401;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MTIQWSLVLFTVLSGCGAGLFACTALDEFRGGAASKVRLPACAVAVALLVVGGIASATHLSHVDRMMAVLAHPTAGIFLEALLLGLLAVCIAVYALLVKREASSGARKALAATGIVLAVAFAFACGVSYMMTSRPVWNTVALPLAYLGTALATGAALYLVMCAALKVDEGDVKKAGVYAAAGGALSLVLTVAFGLVSGTAFGDQAALFWVAVVLCGSAAPAVCGVLVARKSGGALSLGVVALAGALVGSVAVRAVMWLVGTAVANYFGFAL;locus_tag=LOCUS_04010;note=Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-157%2C Eval:3.7e-08%2C score:50.4%2C C-term missing],MGA_401
NODE_4_length_144197_cov_90.594449	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	24195	24824	.	+	0	ID=MGA_402;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MADYTRRAFLGFTAATAALAGVGASAIAFAGEGGLLRPPGGQDEGALVAACVKCDRCRSACPTNVVGVAHVEDGLLQARTPVLDFHKGYCDFCGKCQTACPTGALGSFDPQRDKLGVAVVQKDRCIAYFEGCVECEKACPYEAIALDDVGHPVIDAAKCNGCGVCENVCPALVYRSFAGGSRRGVVVVAPERYERLGRTTVEGESEMIV;locus_tag=LOCUS_04020;note=WP_010943319.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Geobacter sulfurreducens) [pid:37.3%25%2C q_cov:67.5%25%2C s_cov:31.1%25%2C Eval:3.4e-24%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR00402%3B napF: ferredoxin-type protein NapF [Name:TIGR00402%2C Eval:2.8e-21%2C score:74.0%2C bias:11.2],Domain:cl25974:Fer4_21 4Fe-4S dicluster domain. The six subunit complex RnfABCDGE in Rhodobacter capsulatus encodes an apparent NADH oxidoreductase responsible for electron transport to nitrogenase%2C necessary for nitrogen fixation. A closely related complex in E. coli%2C RsxABCDGE (Reducer of SoxR)%2C reduces the 2Fe-2S-containing superoxide sensor SoxR%2C active as a transcription factor when oxidized. This family of putative NADH oxidoreductase complexes exists in many of the same species as the related NQR%2C a Na(+)-translocating NADH-quinone reductase%2C but is distinct. This model describes the B subunit. [Energy metabolism%2C Electron transport] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:117-170%2C Eval:7.9e-10%2C score:54.3%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl25361:NuoI Formate hydrogenlyase subunit 6/NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase 23 kD subunit (chain I) [Energy production and conversion]. See for descriptions of different groups. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:51-124%2C Eval:3.0e-08%2C score:48.6%2C C-term missing],MGA_402
