NODE_4_length_144197_cov_90.594449	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	63400	64449	.	+	0	ID=MGA_434;product=UDP-2%2C4-diacetamido-2%2C4%2C6-trideoxy-beta-L-altropyranose hydrolase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011707836.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_04340;gene=pseG;EC_number=3.6.1.57;note=WP_011707836.1 UDP-2%2C4-diacetamido-2%2C4%2C6-trideoxy-beta-L-altropyranose hydrolase (Aeromonas hydrophila) [pid:26.7%25%2C q_cov:97.7%25%2C s_cov:78.2%25%2C Eval:5.2e-20],Domain:cl28257:SpsG Spore coat polysaccharide biosynthesis protein SpsG%2C predicted glycosyltransferase  [Cell wall/membrane/envelope biogenesis]. This protein is found in association with enzymes involved in the biosynthesis of pseudaminic acid%2C a component of polysaccharide in certain Pseudomonas strains as well as a modification of flagellin in Campylobacter and Hellicobacter. The role of this protein is unclear%2C although it may participate in N-acetylation in conjunction with%2C or in the absence of PseH (TIGR03585) as it often scores above the trusted cutoff to pfam00583 representing a family of acetyltransferases. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:8-343%2C Eval:1.6e-35%2C score:128.8],MGA_434
NODE_4_length_144197_cov_90.594449	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	64446	65657	.	+	0	ID=MGA_435;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_04350;note=WP_000058907.1 alpha-hydroxy-acid oxidizing protein (Leptospira interrogans) [pid:31.3%25%2C q_cov:97.0%25%2C s_cov:51.4%25%2C Eval:5.8e-50%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR01142%3B purT: phosphoribosylglycinamide formyltransferase 2 [Name:TIGR01142%2C Eval:1.9e-14%2C score:51.3%2C bias:0.1],Domain:cl27719:Biotin_carb_N Biotin carboxylase%2C N-terminal domain. Carbamoyl-phosphate synthase (CPSase) catalyzes the first committed step in pyrimidine%2C arginine%2C and urea biosynthesis. In general%2C it is a glutamine-dependent enzyme%2C EC 6.3.5.5%2C termed CPSase II in eukaryotes. An exception is the mammalian mitochondrial urea-cycle form%2C CPSase I%2C in which the glutamine amidotransferase domain active site Cys on the small subunit has been lost%2C and the enzyme is ammonia-dependent. In both CPSase I and the closely related%2C glutamine-dependent CPSase III (allosterically activated by acetyl-glutamate) demonstrated in some other vertebrates%2C the small and large chain regions are fused in a single polypeptide chain. This model represents the large chain of glutamine-hydrolysing carbamoyl-phosphate synthases%2C or the corresponding regions of larger%2C multifunctional proteins%2C as found in all domains of life%2C and CPSase I forms are considered exceptions within the family. In several thermophilic species (Methanobacterium thermoautotrophicum%2C Methanococcus jannaschii%2C Aquifex aeolicus)%2C the large subunit appears split%2C at different points%2C into two separate genes. [Purines%2C pyrimidines%2C nucleosides%2C and nucleotides%2C Pyrimidine ribonucleotide biosynthesis] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:8-396%2C Eval:1.3e-28%2C score:113.5],MGA_435
