NODE_5_length_133089_cov_81.262315	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	74180	75064	.	-	0	ID=MGA_571;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_05700;note=WP_015943352.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:29.8%25%2C q_cov:83.7%25%2C s_cov:49.8%25%2C Eval:2.0e-19%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02163%3B napH_: ferredoxin-type protein%2C NapH/MauN family [Name:TIGR02163%2C Eval:1.3e-23%2C score:81.8%2C bias:4.7],Domain:cl26308:Fer4_5 4Fe-4S binding domain. Most members of this family are the NapH protein%2C found next to NapG%2Cin operons that encode the periplasmic nitrate reductase. Some species with this reductase lack NapC but accomplish electron transfer to NapAB in some other manner%2C likely to involve NapH%2C NapG%2C and/or some other protein. A few members of this protein are designated MauN and are found in methylamine utilization operons in species that appear to lack a periplasmic nitrate reductase. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:59-277%2C Eval:2.8e-16%2C score:75.2%2C C-term missing],MGA_571
NODE_5_length_133089_cov_81.262315	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	75064	75699	.	-	0	ID=MGA_572;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MAAYTRRAFAGFCGAAAVFAAFGGAVKAADGASETALVRPPGAQDELHLLASCVKCDRCRSVCHTGVIGVAEVGDGFLRARTPKLNFHRGSCDFCGDCQRVCPTGAIGAFDPEADKMGMAVVQKDRCVAYYQGCVECQKACPFEAIALDGDGHPVVDADRCNGCGVCEDVCPALVYRSFSGGTRRGIVVVSPSAYARLGKTVVEDESEMSA;locus_tag=LOCUS_05710;note=WP_015943352.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:38.5%25%2C q_cov:66.4%25%2C s_cov:30.2%25%2C Eval:3.8e-23%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR00402%3B napF: ferredoxin-type protein NapF [Name:TIGR00402%2C Eval:3.1e-23%2C score:80.3%2C bias:10.6],Domain:cl25974:Fer4_21 4Fe-4S dicluster domain. The six subunit complex RnfABCDGE in Rhodobacter capsulatus encodes an apparent NADH oxidoreductase responsible for electron transport to nitrogenase%2C necessary for nitrogen fixation. A closely related complex in E. coli%2C RsxABCDGE (Reducer of SoxR)%2C reduces the 2Fe-2S-containing superoxide sensor SoxR%2C active as a transcription factor when oxidized. This family of putative NADH oxidoreductase complexes exists in many of the same species as the related NQR%2C a Na(+)-translocating NADH-quinone reductase%2C but is distinct. This model describes the B subunit. [Energy metabolism%2C Electron transport] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:119-172%2C Eval:2.5e-10%2C score:55.8%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:97-208%2C Eval:2.4e-08%2C score:50.0%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl25361:NuoI Formate hydrogenlyase subunit 6/NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase 23 kD subunit (chain I) [Energy production and conversion]. See for descriptions of different groups. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:53-107%2C Eval:7.4e-08%2C score:47.4%2C C-term missing],MGA_572
