NODE_7_length_121342_cov_76.535414	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	33492	35189	.	-	0	ID=MGA_763;product=FAD-binding protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005813627.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_07610;note=WP_005813627.1 FAD-binding protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:29.5%25%2C q_cov:97.0%25%2C s_cov:97.8%25%2C Eval:2.3e-53],Domain:cl27630:FAD_binding_2 FAD binding domain. This model describes a family of redox proteins related to the succinate dehydrogenases and fumarate reductases of E. coli%2C mitochondria%2C and other well-characterized systems. A member of this family from Shewanella frigidimarina NCIMB400 is characterized as a water-soluble periplasmic protein with four heme groups%2C a non-covalently bound FAD%2C and essentially unidirectional fumarate reductase activity. At least seven distinct members of this family are found in Shewanella oneidensis%2C a species able to use a wide variety of pathways for respiraton. [Energy metabolism%2C Electron transport] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:67-390%2C Eval:3.3e-11%2C score:62.8%2C C-term missing],MGA_763
