NODE_8_length_114051_cov_78.425264	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	8696	9337	.	-	0	ID=MGA_853;product=4Fe-4S dicluster domain-containing protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011388076.1;translation=MRASSPMGRKFVIADPATCIGCKTCMAACFHRHDVPNDVAVPRLTLVTTRTISAPVGCHHCAEAPCVDACPTGCLFTDDEHVGVHPDKCIGCRNCVLACPYGAVEIVTEKLPPEPEAASGTEAAAASAQDDKGARARARAKKRKRTKSTVVKCDLCLDRAGGPACAAACPTKALRLIDAQFMERARQNKRKAAARASASFASMKLNADLDEGE;locus_tag=LOCUS_08490;note=WP_011388076.1 4Fe-4S dicluster domain-containing protein (Rhodospirillum rubrum) [pid:37.4%25%2C q_cov:80.3%25%2C s_cov:86.4%25%2C Eval:7.8e-32],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:9-190%2C Eval:2.9e-29%2C score:104.5],MGA_853
