NODE_8_length_114051_cov_78.425264	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	29997	32093	.	-	0	ID=MGA_874;product=FAD-dependent oxidoreductase;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011461745.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_08700;note=WP_011461745.1 FAD-dependent oxidoreductase (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:55.7%25%2C q_cov:99.7%25%2C s_cov:99.9%25%2C Eval:1.6e-221],Domain:cl21457:ICL_KPHMT N/A. This domain includes the enzyme Phosphoenolpyruvate phosphomutase (EC:5.4.2.9). This protein has been characterized as catalyzing the formation of a carbon-phosphorus bond by converting phosphoenolpyruvate (PEP) to phosphonopyruvate (P-Pyr). This enzyme has a TIM barrel fold. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-368%2C Eval:1.8e-79%2C score:255.2],Domain:cl28234:GltD NADPH-dependent glutamate synthase beta chain or related oxidoreductase [Amino acid transport and metabolism%2C General function prediction only]. This model represents one of three built for the NADPH-dependent or NADH-dependent glutamate synthase (EC 1.4.1.13 and 1.4.1.14%2C respectively) small subunit and homologs. TIGR01317 describes the small subunit (or equivalent region from longer forms) in eukaryotes%2C Gram-positive bacteria%2C and some other lineages%2C both NADH and NADPH-dependent. TIGR01316 describes a protein of similar length%2C from Archaea and a number of bacterial lineages%2C that forms glutamate synthase homotetramers without a large subunit. This model describes both glutatate synthase small subunit and closely related paralogs of unknown function from a number of gamma and alpha subdivision Proteobacteria%2C including E. coli. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:393-566%2C Eval:1.0e-12%2C score:67.7%2C C-term missing],MGA_874
