NODE_8_length_114051_cov_78.425264	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	73045	73938	.	-	0	ID=MGA_910;product=polysulfide reductase NrfD;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005811186.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_09060;gene=nrfD;note=WP_005811186.1 polysulfide reductase NrfD (Desulfitobacterium) [pid:33.8%25%2C q_cov:95.6%25%2C s_cov:96.8%25%2C Eval:1.0e-39],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:4-286%2C Eval:2.3e-29%2C score:110.6],MGA_910
