NODE_10_length_110724_cov_83.649155	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	85819	86718	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1127;product=dimethyl sulfoxide reductase anchor subunit;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_005809896.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_11210;EC_number=1.8.5.3;note=WP_005809896.1 dimethyl sulfoxide reductase anchor subunit (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:25.1%25%2C q_cov:98.3%25%2C s_cov:97.2%25%2C Eval:1.9e-09],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-288%2C Eval:5.1e-10%2C score:56.3],MGA_1127
NODE_10_length_110724_cov_83.649155	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	87065	87730	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1128;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MSEEDEISSKRAKGPLDVSRRALLIGAGSTAALLGLGALRYAGHNPLVRPPGGQDEARLVSACIRCEKCYEACPRGVIVPAHIEDGLLGMRSPALKFDADFCDYCADENGGEPLCVKVCPTEALALPADATAENTLLGLAVIDEAQCLAFRDTGCRYCYDACPYEAIELTGEGANPHVSVLADKCNGCGACESVCVSLKAGSIVSGAQERAIVVKPIESAE;locus_tag=LOCUS_11220;note=WP_010943319.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Geobacter sulfurreducens) [pid:33.7%25%2C q_cov:74.2%25%2C s_cov:33.0%25%2C Eval:7.3e-20%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR00402%3B napF: ferredoxin-type protein NapF [Name:TIGR00402%2C Eval:2.0e-18%2C score:64.7%2C bias:8.8],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:60-196%2C Eval:5.4e-11%2C score:57.1%2C C-term missing],MGA_1128
NODE_10_length_110724_cov_83.649155	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	87740	88756	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1129;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_11230;note=WP_015943352.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Desulfitobacterium hafniense) [pid:24.0%25%2C q_cov:95.9%25%2C s_cov:57.2%25%2C Eval:2.2e-15%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02163%3B napH_: ferredoxin-type protein%2C NapH/MauN family [Name:TIGR02163%2C Eval:2.7e-17%2C score:61.1%2C bias:25.1],Domain:cl26308:Fer4_5 4Fe-4S binding domain. Most members of this family are the NapH protein%2C found next to NapG%2Cin operons that encode the periplasmic nitrate reductase. Some species with this reductase lack NapC but accomplish electron transfer to NapAB in some other manner%2C likely to involve NapH%2C NapG%2C and/or some other protein. A few members of this protein are designated MauN and are found in methylamine utilization operons in species that appear to lack a periplasmic nitrate reductase. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:12-313%2C Eval:9.7e-08%2C score:50.2%2C C-term missing],MGA_1129
NODE_10_length_110724_cov_83.649155	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	88756	89937	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1130;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_11240;note=WP_011088232.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Bradyrhizobium diazoefficiens) [pid:26.5%25%2C q_cov:80.4%25%2C s_cov:45.7%25%2C Eval:1.4e-16%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02700%3B flavo_MJ0208: archaeoflavoprotein%2C MJ0208 family [Name:TIGR02700%2C Eval:2.2e-17%2C score:61.1%2C bias:19.6],Domain:cl25361:NuoI Formate hydrogenlyase subunit 6/NADH:ubiquinone oxidoreductase 23 kD subunit (chain I) [Energy production and conversion]. See for descriptions of different groups. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:294-348%2C Eval:4.1e-10%2C score:55.5%2C C-term missing],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:29-89%2C Eval:5.8e-09%2C score:53.9%2C C-term missing],MGA_1130
