NODE_14_length_97060_cov_54.730241	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	50468	50674	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1464;product=4Fe-4S binding protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_003420706.1;translation=MARISVDDSFCKGCGLCVDACPEQIMALDRDKITVKGYHPAYCTDLDACTGCMSCAVMCPDVAITVER;locus_tag=LOCUS_14550;note=WP_003420706.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Clostridioides) [pid:56.1%25%2C q_cov:97.1%25%2C s_cov:93.0%25%2C Eval:1.1e-17],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-68%2C Eval:4.1e-09%2C score:47.7%2C C-term missing],MGA_1464
