NODE_15_length_87708_cov_86.146044	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	18291	19283	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1529;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_15180;note=WP_011706568.1 cytochrome c nitrite reductase subunit NrfD (Aeromonas hydrophila) [pid:26.6%25%2C q_cov:57.0%25%2C s_cov:54.3%25%2C Eval:4.2e-08%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR03148%3B cyt_nit_nrfD: cytochrome c nitrite reductase%2C NrfD subunit [Name:TIGR03148%2C Eval:1.9e-24%2C score:84.5%2C bias:23.1],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:4-315%2C Eval:6.0e-20%2C score:85.5],MGA_1529
NODE_15_length_87708_cov_86.146044	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	19285	19611	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1530;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MKVCPAGAISKDAHGIVKVNPDVCIGCKYCFQACPYEVPKYNSVSMDKCDCCQGSGVAIGEDPYCVRVCKFGALQFGPLDELMELTNHSAVPVAQANGPSCLVLGTEK;locus_tag=LOCUS_15190;note=WP_013096798.1 dimethylsulfoxide reductase subunit B (Enterobacter cloacae) [pid:47.2%25%2C q_cov:94.4%25%2C s_cov:52.2%25%2C Eval:1.4e-20%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR02951%3B DMSO_dmsB: dimethylsulfoxide reductase%2C chain B [Name:TIGR02951%2C Eval:2.7e-24%2C score:84.0%2C bias:7.6],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:1-86%2C Eval:1.2e-25%2C score:92.1%2C N-term missing],MGA_1530
