NODE_15_length_87708_cov_86.146044	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	59939	60841	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1565;product=polysulfide reductase NrfD;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011073772.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_15540;gene=nrfD;note=WP_011073772.1 polysulfide reductase NrfD (Shewanella oneidensis) [pid:25.6%25%2C q_cov:90.3%25%2C s_cov:89.5%25%2C Eval:4.6e-11],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:37-284%2C Eval:9.0e-17%2C score:76.3],MGA_1565
