NODE_19_length_69235_cov_53.114867	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	201	422	.	+	0	ID=MGA_1806;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MTVKRNSLSLCIGCGTCAKICPMDVMRFDASSAKSVIAYPENCQSCGQCYLNCPNDSLGIDATMYTYGLVTTR;locus_tag=LOCUS_17940;note=WP_081423266.1 4Fe-4S binding protein (Archaeoglobus fulgidus) [pid:50.9%25%2C q_cov:72.6%25%2C s_cov:73.9%25%2C Eval:2.3e-10%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR04395%3B cutC_activ_rSAM: choline TMA-lyase-activating enzyme [Name:TIGR04395%2C Eval:1.4e-09%2C score:35.6%2C bias:2.3],Domain:cl27605:NIR_SIR Nitrite and sulphite reductase 4Fe-4S domain. Dissimilatory sulfite reductase catalyzes the six-electron reduction of sulfite to sulfide%2C as the terminal reaction in dissimilatory sulfate reduction. It remains unclear however%2C whether trithionate and thiosulfate serve as intermediate compounds to sulfide%2C or as end products of sulfite reduction. Sulfite reductase is a multisubunit enzyme composed of dimers of either alpha/beta or alpha/beta/gamma subunits%2C each containing a siroheme and iron sulfur cluster prosthetic center. Found in sulfate-reducing bacteria%2C these genes are commonly located in an unidirectional gene cluster. This model describes the alpha subunit of sulfite reductase. [Central intermediary metabolism%2C Sulfur metabolism] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:10-56%2C Eval:8.6e-08%2C score:44.3%2C C-term missing],MGA_1806
