NODE_26_length_52620_cov_50.152504	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	33984	34769	.	+	0	ID=MGA_2189;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;translation=MTETNQRATDAQHKGGLSRRQFIAGIGGLGIGAVLGSGITALLLPDDVYAIEASQGYLLVDAKKCAGCETCVISCSLAHLGRINTSLSRIQVMKNALGSFPSDDVMQNQCRQCPYPSCVEACPVGAMHADPETGVRLVDEGKCIGCERCVEACPFTPSRVQWNFEDKHAQKCDLCKNTPFWDEEGGPSGKQLCVEICPMKAIAFTNVLPVQTDEGYTANLRNDHYLEIGLPSDDEARIPPARLGYGAGGTAAQAAAGSNDK;locus_tag=LOCUS_21750;note=WP_004083227.1 4Fe-4S dicluster domain-containing protein (Thermotoga) [pid:37.7%25%2C q_cov:57.5%25%2C s_cov:94.7%25%2C Eval:7.5e-20%2C partial hit],TIGR:TIGR03149%3B cyt_nit_nrfC: cytochrome c nitrite reductase%2C Fe-S protein [Name:TIGR03149%2C Eval:1.9e-30%2C score:103.8%2C bias:5.4],Domain:cl25360:DMSOR_beta-like Beta subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. This family consists of the small beta iron-sulfur (FeS) subunit of the DMSO Reductase (DMSOR) family. Members of this family also contain a large%2C periplasmic molybdenum-containing alpha subunit and may have a small gamma subunit as well.  Examples of heterodimeric members with alpha and beta subunits include arsenite oxidase%2C and tungsten-containing formate dehydrogenase (FDH-T) while   heterotrimeric members containing alpha%2C beta%2C and gamma subunits include formate dehydrogenase-N (FDH-N)%2C and nitrate reductase (NarGHI).  The beta subunit contains four Fe4/S4 and/or Fe3/S4 clusters which transfer the electrons from the alpha subunit to a hydrophobic integral membrane protein%2C presumably a cytochrome containing two b-type heme groups. The reducing equivalents are then transferred to menaquinone%2C which finally reduces the electron-accepting enzyme system. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:58-204%2C Eval:2.5e-29%2C score:107.1%2C C-term missing],MGA_2189
NODE_26_length_52620_cov_50.152504	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	34782	36824	.	+	0	ID=MGA_2190;product=hypothetical protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator;;locus_tag=LOCUS_21760;note=WP_012869226.1 aldehyde ferredoxin oxidoreductase family protein (Thermanaerovibrio acidaminovorans) [pid:33.3%25%2C q_cov:36.3%25%2C s_cov:37.2%25%2C Eval:2.6e-30%2C partial hit],Domain:cl27384:AFOR_C Aldehyde ferredoxin oxidoreductase%2C domains 2 %26amp%3B 3. Aldehyde ferredoxin oxidoreductase (AOR) catalyzes the reversible oxidation of aldehydes to their corresponding carboxylic acids with their accompanying reduction of the redox protein ferredoxin. This family is composed of two structural domains that bind the tungsten cofactor via DXXGL(C/D) motifs. In addition to maintaining specific binding interactions with the cofactor%2C another role for domains 2 and 3 may be to regulate substrate access to AOR. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:5-667%2C Eval:1.1e-84%2C score:276.1],MGA_2190
