NODE_28_length_50388_cov_66.695494	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	40609	41844	.	-	0	ID=MGA_2276;product=polysulfide reductase NrfD;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_041272584.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_22600;gene=nrfD;note=WP_041272584.1 polysulfide reductase NrfD (Desulfitobacterium) [pid:58.5%25%2C q_cov:88.6%25%2C s_cov:90.5%25%2C Eval:4.2e-120],Domain:cl21513:NrfD Polysulphide reductase%2C NrfD. Bacterial polysulfide reductase is an integral membrane protein complex responsible for quinone-coupled reduction of polysulfide%2C a process important in extreme environments such as deep-sea vents and hot springs. Polysulfides are a class of compounds composed of chains of sulfur atoms%2C which in their simplest form are present as an anion with general formula Sn(2-). In nature%2C polysulfides are found in particularly high concentrations in extreme volcanic or geothermically active environments. Here%2C the reduction and oxidation of polysulfides are vital processes for many bacteria and are essential steps in the global sulfur cycle. In particular%2C the reduction of polysulfide to hydrogen sulfide in these environments is usually linked to energy-generating respiratory processes%2C supporting growth of many microorganisms%2C particularly hyperthermophiles. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:26-385%2C Eval:5.9e-52%2C score:176.2],MGA_2276
