NODE_72_length_3059_cov_43.210262	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	236	1069	.	-	0	ID=MGA_2901;product=DUF364 domain-containing protein;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011392938.1;translation=MKRSENEAVRRPDTRDDATPWKLYNRLIEGIPEDIAVRDYCLGTHWSYVEADCGMGVSFTCKGGSRRACKQDLRGTGLREMAELAKSWCFEEATLGVAALNAYYARKELLDPLGATYDEPIELPDGTVRKMDAFELYRPRIEASERKNVTVVGHFPHVDRIAEYANLTVLERNCSQELDTPDPACEYVLPDTDFAFITGVTIINKTAPRLLELARNATTVLVGPSVVMSSVLFEQGADALAGSVVADPEKTRFAIKNGAGQFFGEALQMTMIERDRA;locus_tag=LOCUS_28710;note=WP_011392938.1 DUF364 domain-containing protein (Moorella thermoacetica) [pid:38.7%25%2C q_cov:92.1%25%2C s_cov:87.2%25%2C Eval:6.2e-44],Domain:cl27201:DUF364 Putative heavy-metal chelation. This domain of unknown function has a PLP-dependent transferase-like fold. Its genomic context suggests that it may have a role in anaerobic vitamin B12 biosynthesis. This domain is often found at the C-terminus of proteins containing DUF4213%2C pfam13938. The structure of UnioProtKB:B8FUJ5%2C Structure 3l5o%2C suggests that the protein has an enolase N-terminal-like fold and this Rossmann-like C-terminal domain. Structural and bioinformatic analyses reveal partial similarities to Rossmann-like methyltransferases%2C with residues from the enolase-like fold combining to form a unique active site that is likely to be involved in the condensation or hydrolysis of molecules implicated in the synthesis of flavins%2C pterins or other siderophores. The protein may be playing a role in heavy-metal chelation. [Superfamily%2C Aligned:28-266%2C Eval:4.4e-20%2C score:84.1],MGA_2901
